fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">core concept of servant-leadership. </div><div class="t m382 x13 h23 y8bf ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read Romans 12:1-3. What is the &quot;measure of faith&quot; spoken of </div><div class="t m4e5 xa h23 y8c0 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in verse 3? What does Paul mean by the words, &quot;Think of yourself </div><div class="t m19c xa h23 y761 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with sober judgment&quot; (Rom. 12:3, NIV)? </div><div class="t m5b0 x13 h1b y8c1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The key Greek word for &quot;servant&quot; is </div><div class="t m1c8 x99 h1b y8c1 ff5 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">doulos, </div><div class="t m297 x27 h1b y8c1 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">which also means </div><div class="t m5b1 xa h1b y8c2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;slave.&quot; A true Christian leader is a voluntary &quot;slave&quot; to Jesus and to </div><div class="t m5b2 xa h1b y481 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">those whom he or she wishes to serve. (See Rom. 1:1; 1 Cor 9:19.) </div><div class="t m246 x9b h1b y8c3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This perspective on leadership produces an attitude of servanthood on </div><div class="t m137 x9b h1b y8c4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the part of the leader. The key concepts of servant leadership are: </div><div class="t m40f xd h23 y8c5 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Text </div><div class="t m11e x30 h23 y5ae ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Principle </div><div class="t m2ad xb h37 y8c6 ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John 13:35 </div><div class="t m321 x4c h37 y8c7 ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;All men will know that you are my disciples if you love </div><div class="t m40c x4c h37 y8c8 ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">one another&quot; (NIV). </div><div class="t m14c xb h37 y22e ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mark 9:33-35 </div><div class="t m193 xb9 h37 y3ad ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is serving, not commanding. </div><div class="t m3e2 xb h37 y10e ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rom. 12:3 </div><div class="t m193 xb9 h37 y8c9 ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is being respectful, not looking down on others. </div><div class="t m199 xb h37 y8ca ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 Peter 5:3 </div><div class="t m1ad xb9 h37 y8cb ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is being exemplary, not domineering. </div><div class="t m40f xb h37 y8cc ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rom. 12:10 </div><div class="t m5b3 xb9 h37 y8cd ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is being equal, not superior. </div><div class="t m262 xb h37 y8ce ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eph. 5:21 </div><div class="t m177 xb9 h37 y8cf ff4 fs19 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It is being submissive, not coercive. </div><div class="t m4fd x3a h23 y8d0 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Think about some leaders you have known and your own </div><div class="t m14b xb h23 y8d1 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">leadership efforts. How do they and you match the principles </div><div class="t m160 xb h23 y8d2 ff3 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">presented in this lesson? </div><div class="t m470 xb2 h1b y8d3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">65 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
